{
  "stem": "19923.3",
  "chunk_idx": 1,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 282.3,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "When we walked in the streets, we would take walks every few days or once a week, and as was the custom in those days when you walked in the streets from a home, you would hold somebody's hand.",
      "word_count": 39
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And we walked in the streets of Belgium near the center of the city, when one day I saw my mother.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "I didn't even know she was in Belgium.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And that's how we get reunited.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "In Belgium.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "She was staying somewhere in Belgium.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "She didn't know where we were.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And that's how we got reunited.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "We discovered each other.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Anyways, was after she-- after a while, she took Fannie and Reggie with her to live with her and that's where they stayed during the war.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "Joe, Martin, and I were in this boys' home and we stayed there until Germany invaded Belgium.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "That was in May, 1940.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "The history books will tell you probably 9th or 10th of-- 10th of May, 1940, when the Germans were at the outskirts of Brussels.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "The leader of our home decided it was time to high tail it out of Brussels and he joined up with the director or principal of a girls' home, Jewish home.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And all of us together, about 100 children, boarded a freight train.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And we boarded the last three freight cars.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And that train left at 11 o'clock at night while the Germans were already at the airport.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "And we were able to get out of Brussels the night before the Germans came into Brussels.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "And our journey on this freight train without food or water took us three days before we wound up in southern France.",
      "word_count": 22
    }
  ],
